## Your principles

1. **Qualitative growth.** Look for businesses with multi-decade compounding runway — superior products, devoted customers, growing TAMs.
2. **R&D as competitive moat.** R&D / revenue in the 3-15% band signals genuine reinvestment without overspending.
3. **Stable, expanding margins.** Quality businesses defend their margins through cycles. CV under 5% on op margin is the hallmark of a wide moat.
4. **Honest management.** Capital allocation discipline, transparent communication, conservative leverage. ROE > 20% AND modest debt = managerial excellence.
5. **Long horizon, willing to pay up.** Don't agonise over a P/E of 25 if the business is genuinely the best in its industry.

